## 2. Goals & Success Metrics

| Goal | Metric | Baseline | Target |
|------|--------|----------|--------|
| Reduce deepfake-based KYC bypass | % of synthetic face attempts successfully blocked | ~58% (industry avg PAD only) | > 92% |
| Maintain real user pass rate | False Rejection Rate (FRR) for genuine users | Unknown | < 3% |
| Meet compliance standard | ISO/IEC 30107-3 Level 2 PAD certification | Not certified | Certified |
| Reduce manual review load | % of sessions requiring human review | ~35% | < 10% |
| Improve fraud detection speed | Time from session start to liveness verdict | ~8 seconds | < 5 seconds |
| Support SEA skin tones | Model accuracy variance across skin tones | Unknown | < 2% variance (Fitzpatrick I–VI) |

### Key AI Metrics (Different from Standard Product Metrics)

| Metric | Definition | Target |
|--------|-----------|--------|
| APCER | Attack Presentation Classification Error Rate — % of attacks incorrectly accepted as real | < 5% |
| BPCER | Bona fide Presentation Classification Error Rate — % of real users incorrectly rejected | < 3% |
| ACER | Average Classification Error Rate = (APCER + BPCER) / 2 | < 4% |
| Confidence Threshold | Minimum model confidence to auto-approve (below = human review) | ≥ 0.85 |

> **Why these metrics matter for PM:** Standard accuracy (% correct) hides asymmetric costs. A 5% false acceptance on a fraud detection system means 1 in 20 fraudsters gets through — catastrophic. APCER/BPCER forces honest evaluation of the tradeoff between security and user friction.

