## 3. User Personas

### Persona A — Legitimate New Merchant / Customer (Primary)
- Thai or Cambodian individual onboarding to a fintech platform for the first time
- Varies in age (20–55), lighting conditions, device quality, and internet speed
- Pain point: Existing liveness checks fail or ask them to repeat prompts 3–4 times due to environment
- Needs: Fast, frictionless verification that works on a mid-range Android in natural Thai light conditions

### Persona B — Fraudster (Adversary Persona)
- Operates in organised fraud networks in Thailand/Cambodia border regions
- Has access to: DeepFaceLive, StyleGAN-generated faces, dark web fake ID templates, virtual camera software
- Attack workflow: Generate synthetic face → match to stolen ID → use virtual camera plugin to inject video into verification stream
- Motivation: Open mule accounts for money laundering / social engineering scams

### Persona C — Compliance Officer (Internal)
- Reviews flagged sessions in the human-review queue
- Needs: Clear confidence scores, visual evidence of why session was flagged, audit trail
- Pain point: Too many false positives creating manual review backlog

### Persona D — Platform Integration Engineer (B2B)
- Developer at a fintech partner integrating the liveness SDK into their mobile KYC flow
- Needs: Clear SDK documentation, webhook events, sandbox environment, error codes
- Pain point: Black-box liveness APIs with no explainability — cannot debug failed sessions

