## 4. User Stories

### Legitimate User Flow

**US-001**
As a **new user**, I want the liveness check to complete in under 5 seconds with clear visual guidance, so that I can pass verification without re-attempting multiple times due to environment or confusion.

**US-002**
As a **user in low-light conditions**, I want the system to prompt me to improve lighting rather than silently failing, so that I know what to do to complete verification.

**US-003**
As a **user with a darker skin tone (Fitzpatrick IV–VI)**, I want the model to perform with the same accuracy as for lighter skin tones, so that I am not disproportionately rejected due to model bias.

### Platform / Compliance Flow

**US-004**
As a **compliance officer**, I want to see a confidence breakdown for every flagged session (which signals triggered the flag), so that I can make an informed human review decision in under 30 seconds.

**US-005**
As a **compliance officer**, I want sessions that score between 0.70–0.84 confidence (below auto-approve threshold) to be automatically queued for human review, so that borderline cases are not silently rejected or accepted.

**US-006**
As an **integration engineer**, I want a webhook event fired for every liveness verdict, so that my platform can update the KYC state in real time without polling.

