## 7. Non-Functional Requirements

| Category | Requirement |
|----------|-------------|
| Latency | End-to-end liveness verdict in < 5 seconds (p95) |
| Availability | 99.95% uptime — KYC blocking flow, no downtime acceptable |
| Security | All biometric data encrypted in transit (TLS 1.3) and at rest (AES-256). Biometric data deleted within 30 days post-verification per PDPA Thailand |
| Compliance | ISO/IEC 30107-3 Level 2 PAD certification. Thailand PDPA (Personal Data Protection Act B.E. 2562). Bank of Thailand eKYC guidelines |
| Privacy | Biometric data is sensitive under Thailand PDPA — explicit consent required before capture. Data minimisation: store only what is needed for audit, not full video |
| Bias / Fairness | APCER/BPCER variance < 2% across Fitzpatrick I–VI skin tone groups |
| Accessibility | Visual + audio guidance available. Works with screen reader navigation up to the camera capture step |
| Device Support | iOS 13+ and Android 8+ (API Level 26+). Minimum supported camera: 720p at 24fps |
| Localisation | Thai, Khmer (Cambodian), and English UI prompts |

