## 9. Edge Cases & Out of Scope

### Edge Cases

| Scenario | Expected Behaviour |
|----------|-------------------|
| User wearing glasses | Allow. Do not penalise. Glasses are common and model must be trained to handle them. Note: sunglasses → prompt user to remove for liveness check. |
| Low-light environment | Prompt user with guidance: "Please move to a brighter area." After 2 prompts, route to REVIEW with note "poor lighting conditions" — do not auto-reject. |
| User with facial hair, makeup, or face paint | Allow normal flow. Model should be trained on diverse appearances. Flag only if beard/makeup is inconsistent with ID document photo (document-face match is a separate module). |
| Partial face obstruction (e.g., mask) | Prompt: "Please remove any face covering to continue." If user cannot (medical reason), route to manual review. |
| Identical twins | Liveness detection confirms a real person is present — does not confirm identity match. Identity matching against ID document is a separate concern. |
| Very slow internet connection | Capture frames locally, batch upload. Do not fail session due to upload latency. Show progress indicator. |
| Model inference service unavailable | Fail-secure: route all sessions to manual review. Do NOT auto-approve. Alert on-call ML engineer. |
| User is a minor (< 18) | Liveness detection runs normally. Age verification and parental consent is handled by a separate module — out of scope for this PRD. |

### Out of Scope (v1.0)

- **Voice liveness detection** — audio deepfake detection is a separate product surface (planned v1.3)
- **Document liveness / tamper detection** — detecting AI-generated fake IDs is a separate pipeline (planned v1.2)
- **Continuous authentication** — re-verifying user liveness during an active session (planned v2.0)
- **Emotion/state detection** — detecting if user is under duress (planned v2.0)
- **Gen 4 injection attack resistance** — full cryptographic injection defense requires hardware-level integration beyond v1.0 scope
- **Face matching against ID document** — comparison of liveness face to submitted ID photo is handled by a separate identity module

