## Appendix C: Regulatory Reference

| Regulation | Relevance |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Thailand PDPA (B.E. 2562)** | Biometric data is sensitive personal data — requires explicit consent, purpose limitation, and secure storage. Deletion within 30 days post-verification unless legally required to retain. |
| **Bank of Thailand eKYC Guidelines** | BOT Notification 2563 requires 2-step KYC including biometric identity verification for e-money service operators. Liveness detection fulfills the "verify" step. |
| **ISO/IEC 30107-3** | International standard for Presentation Attack Detection testing. Level 2 certification requires third-party lab testing. APCER/BPCER are defined in this standard. |
| **CEN/TS 18099** | European technical specification for Injection Attack Detection. Relevant if platform operates in EU or has EU merchant customers. |
| **EU AI Act (2024)** | Biometric identification systems are classified as high-risk. Requires transparency documentation, accuracy reporting, and human oversight mechanisms. |
